    {
      "step_idx": 6,
      "role": "InformationVerification_Expert",
      "content": "It appears that the function `scrape_wikipedia_tables` did not return any data. This might indicate that the discography section is not in a table format on the Wikipedia page.\n\nTo handle this, we can extract the text content from the relevant section of the Wikipedia page and parse it manually to identify the studio albums published between 2000 and 2009.\n\nI'll write a Python script to scrape the text content of the Wikipedia page, locate the discography section, and then extract the album names and release years.\n\n```python\nimport requests\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\n\n# URL of the Wikipedia page\nurl = \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercedes_Sosa\"\n\n# Fetch the page content\nresponse = requests.get(url)\nsoup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')\n\n# Locate the discography section\ndiscography_section = soup.find('span', id='Discography')\ndiscography_content = discography_section.find_next('ul')\n\n# Extract album names and release years\nalbums = []\nfor li in discography_content.find_all('li'):\n    text = li.get_text()\n    if any(year in text for year in map(str, range(2000, 2010))):\n        albums.append(text)\n\nprint(albums)\n```\n\nComputer_terminal, please run this code to extract the album names and release years from the discography section of the Wikipedia page for Mercedes Sosa."
