    {
      "step_idx": 8,
      "role": "InformationVerification_Expert",
      "content": "It seems the specific element with id 'Discography' was not found, leading to the error. This may be due to differences in section headers or formatting on the Wikipedia page.\n\nLet's adjust the approach to search for a broader range of potential section headers and ensure we can capture the discography section text properly.\n\nI'll look for headers that might contain the term \"Discography\" and extract the relevant content:\n\n```python\nimport requests\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\n\n# URL of the Wikipedia page\nurl = \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercedes_Sosa\"\n\n# Fetch the page content\nresponse = requests.get(url)\nsoup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')\n\n# Function to find the relevant section\ndef find_section(soup, header_text):\n    for header in soup.find_all(['h2', 'h3', 'h4']):\n        if header_text.lower() in header.get_text().lower():\n            return header.find_next_sibling('ul')\n    return None\n\n# Locate the discography section\ndiscography_content = find_section(soup, \"Discography\")\n\n# Extract album names and release years\nalbums = []\nif discography_content:\n    for li in discography_content.find_all('li'):\n        text = li.get_text()\n        if any(year in text for year in map(str, range(2000, 2010))):\n            albums.append(text)\n\nprint(albums)\n```\n\nComputer_terminal, please run this code to extract the album names and release years from the Wikipedia page for Mercedes Sosa."
